  "prompt": "Has anyone ever tried Nikola Tesla's cosmic energy collector? What were the results?",
  "response": "Nikola Tesla's concept of a cosmic energy collector, often referred to as a radiant energy receiver or cosmic ray collector, is one of his more speculative and less-documented inventions. Tesla believed that it was possible to harness the ambient energy present in the environment, including cosmic rays and other forms of radiant energy, to generate usable electrical power.\n\nThere are no widely recognized or scientifically validated accounts of successful attempts to replicate Tesla's cosmic energy collector. While various inventors, researchers, and enthusiasts have explored Tesla's ideas and tried to build devices based on his concepts, these efforts have not led to any breakthroughs that are accepted by the mainstream scientific community.\n\nResults from these experiments have varied, with some individuals reporting anecdotal success but lacking rigorous scientific validation. The lack of reproducible results and peer-reviewed documentation has left Tesla's cosmic energy collector in the realm of speculative and experimental technology rather than established science.\n\nIn summary, while Tesla's ideas have inspired many to explore the potential of radiant energy, there is no concrete evidence or widely accepted demonstration of a successful cosmic energy collector that harnesses energy in the way Tesla envisioned.",
